Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.45,0:02:06.33,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:121455,126335}The audition for the role\Nof Helen Keller has passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.33,0:02:12.79,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:126335,132799}The five chosen candidates\Nhave each gone through very strict tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.79,0:02:20.22,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:132799,140223}Maya has earned the role of Helen Keller\Nin the form of a double casting with Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.22,0:02:27.23,Episode title,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:141224,147230}{\an5\pos(766,720)\fscy95\blur1\fad(800,0)}—Episode 20—\NThe Two Helens
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.52,0:02:34.19,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:150525,154196}A few days later, the cast for "The Miracle Worker"\Nwere introduced to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.57,0:02:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:154571,157032}Now, let me introduce\Nthe cast members.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.90,0:02:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:157908,160285}Annie Sullivan will be played\Nby Himekawa Utako.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.12,0:02:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:162120,165290}For Mr. Keller, the father's role,\NJinno Tatsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.29,0:02:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:165290,168126}For Kate, the mother,\NMatsumaya Michie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.12,0:02:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:168126,171380}Now, let me introduce\Nthe two Helens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.38,0:02:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:171380,172798}Himekawa Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.79,0:02:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:172798,174549}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.54,0:02:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:174549,175801}Kitajima Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:02:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:175801,176593}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.72,0:03:02.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:179721,182307}I can never win\Nagainst Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.30,0:03:05.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:182307,185018}Kitajima Maya,\NI won't be defeated by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:194403,196029}Hey, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.23,0:03:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:197239,198323}Congratulations\Non your new role.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:198323,199408}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.40,0:03:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:199408,202327}This is an important play for\NMetropolitan Entertainment's new building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.32,0:03:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:202327,204037}Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.03,0:03:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:204037,208125}Of course I will, so that the young president,\NMr. Masumi, can't make fun of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.96,0:03:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:210961,213046}Look at me, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.04,0:03:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:213046,215882}Hayami Masumi of Metropolitan\NEntertainment is talking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.42,0:03:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:217426,220804}In this business, greetings and politeness\Nare much more important than acting itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.80,0:03:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:220804,222931}If you don't like me,\Nthen that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.93,0:03:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:222931,224850}Just don't show\Nyour personal emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.85,0:03:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:224850,231606}If people don't like you, then you're\Ndone for regardless of your talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:232482,234526}Now, remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.66,0:04:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:245662,249499}I didn't know you were\Nso kind, Mr. Masumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.49,0:04:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:249499,254463}I have never seen you\Ngiving advice to an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.46,0:04:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:254463,259426}Our reputation will be affected if any one\Nof our actresses doesn't have manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.59,0:04:23.76,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:260594,263764}Practice started the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.76,0:04:30.39,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:263764,270395}A 7 year-old Helen Keller has lost three of her\Nsenses due to high fevers, and was raised selfishly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.39,0:04:34.85,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:270395,274858}Her young teacher, Annie Sullivan,\Nteaches her how to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.77,0:04:39.90,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:275776,279905}Ms. Sullivan tries to use violence to teach her\Nsome manners and how to write,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.90,0:04:46.82,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:279905,286828}but Helen doesn't understand\Nwhy Ms. Sullivan does such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:51.37,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:287704,291374}However, with time, Ms. Sullivan's\Npassion would be rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.37,0:04:54.37,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:291374,294377}When one day Helen touched\Nrunning water from a well,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.37,0:04:57.00,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:294377,297005}she learned that\Nit was a thing called "water".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.00,0:05:01.63,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:297005,301635}Since then, she understood\Nthat things have names.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.63,0:05:06.26,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:301635,306264}She also realized that Ms. Sullivan\Nwas trying to teach her that all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.72,0:05:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:306723,310852}Please keep my advice\Nin mind when acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.85,0:05:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:310852,312103}Does anyone\Nhave any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.48,0:05:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:313480,315607}Yes, what about Helen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.60,0:05:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:315607,318109}Oh, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.10,0:05:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:318109,320904}I doubt that\Nyou need my advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.90,0:05:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:320904,324825}You have Miss Tsukikage,\Na great teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:325784,331540}If I gave advice to you, I might\Nspoil your free-willed acting style.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.87,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:333875,337754}Hey, Mr. Onodera is not going to give\Nany advice to that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:337754,341466}It must be revenge against Tsukikage, who doesn't\Ngive up the play rights for "The Crimson Goddess".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.46,0:05:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:341466,344845}Hey, Ayumi,\Nabout Helen's act.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.84,0:05:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:344845,346471}About how Helen should act?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.47,0:05:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:346471,347514}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.51,0:05:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:347514,349057}Then please…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.05,0:05:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:349057,350141}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.64,0:05:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:351643,356690}Please give me the same advice\Nyou gave to the other Helen, Mr. Onodera.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.73,0:05:58.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:357732,358775}Ayumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.40,0:06:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:359401,361695}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.69,0:06:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:361695,363238}D-Do what you want, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.78,0:06:06.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:363780,366199}Ayumi… What a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.19,0:06:07.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:366199,367909}She's always so confident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.70,0:06:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:369703,370996}No, Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.95,0:06:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:375959,378753}Hey, did you hear that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.75,0:06:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:378753,380881}It didn't seem\Nlike she was acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.17,0:06:26.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382173,386428}{\t(2962,3962,\1c&H101010&\3c&H101010&\4c&H101010&)}I'm no equal to Ayumi…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.26,0:06:35.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393268,395437}Double casted\Nevery other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.43,0:06:38.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395437,398023}I'll be compared with Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.02,0:06:41.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:398023,401943}Ayumi, who I can't even come close to\Nno matter how hard I try.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.44,0:06:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:404446,405530}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.53,0:06:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:405530,406656}Sakurakōji.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.90,0:06:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:408909,412120}I was on my way\Nto your apartment…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.28,0:06:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:413288,415081}But I saw you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:07:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:416124,420962}Sakurakōji,\Nyou seem taller than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.96,0:07:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:420962,422339}You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.84,0:07:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:428845,431848}I haven't seen you for so long.\NHow have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.43,0:07:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:432432,434267}Fine.\NHow about you, Sakurakōji?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.39,0:07:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:435393,437311}You thought about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.31,0:07:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:437311,439189}Of course. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.53,0:07:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:452535,455914}I will be acting in\N"The Miracle Worker".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.91,0:07:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:455914,458041}Yeah, I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.04,0:07:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:458041,459876}It's a double cast with Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.87,0:07:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:459876,460961}I heard that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.71,0:07:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:468718,470011}W-What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.80,0:07:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:470804,475308}We finally get to see each other\Nand this is how you act, Sakurakōji?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:475808,476559}M-Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.89,0:08:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:481898,482899}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.44,0:08:09.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:487445,489906}I still like you, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.61,0:08:13.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:491616,493243}I like you just\Nthe way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.53,0:08:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:493535,494577}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.83,0:08:21.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:497831,501876}I like you when you're smiling\Nlike an ordinary girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.87,0:08:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:501876,503503}Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.83,0:08:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:504838,505964}Sakurakōji…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.21,0:08:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:508216,509384}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:509884,510969}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.97,0:08:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:512971,514305}I've got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.31,0:08:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:529319,530572}Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.95,0:08:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:537954,539873}I have to go. It's late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.75,0:09:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:541750,544209}That's right.\NI'll walk you home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.20,0:09:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:544209,545754}No, that's okay.\NIt's close.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.38,0:09:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:549382,550175}Have to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.17,0:09:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:550175,551051}M-Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.05,0:09:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:551051,553553}See you later, Sakurakōji.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.55,0:09:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:553553,554429}Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.73,0:09:31.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:569736,571237}See you later, see you…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.23,0:09:34.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:571237,574365}When can I see you, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.15,0:09:38.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:575158,578953}You're always busy\Nwith acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.95,0:09:41.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:578953,581831}It's always me\Nwho has to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.91,0:09:47.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:583917,587921}Oh, why is my heart\Nbeating so fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.92,0:09:51.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:587921,591007}He just grabbed my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.71,0:09:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:591716,593009}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.51,0:09:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:593510,597680}Why won't you teach her\Nhow to act like Helen?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:10:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:598056,601518}She's right.\NMaya will be compared…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.51,0:10:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:601518,603603}…with Ayumi everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.93,0:10:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603937,608066}I heard that Ayumi\Nis not getting any help either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.60,0:10:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:608608,611861}But, she has Mr. Onodera,\Na well-known director.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.86,0:10:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:611861,618076}That's okay. About the only thing\Nhe can do is to ignore Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.07,0:10:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:618076,623081}And Maya will act even better\Nif she's ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.24,0:10:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:623248,627836}This play will be a battle\Nbetween Ayumi and Maya's talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.83,0:10:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:627836,630964}And I'm so looking forward\Nto the outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.80,0:10:39.38,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:635802,639389}The battle between\NMaya and Ayumi had already began.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.05,0:10:44.51,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:643059,644519}Backstage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.39,0:10:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:647397,651317}Are you sure you don't want\Nto see Ayumi's practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.31,0:10:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:651317,652152}Yes, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.86,0:10:57.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:652861,657740}If I see how Ayumi acts, then I will\Nremember the Helen played by Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.74,0:10:59.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:657740,659242}I'm afraid of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.24,0:11:01.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:659242,661619}My Helen and her Helen\Nare different.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.74,0:11:06.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:662745,666875}However Ayumi will play her Helen,\Nit's not my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.16,0:11:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:669169,670753}Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.75,0:11:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:670753,672255}Your Helen was really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.25,0:11:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:672255,673965}You were wonderful, Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.96,0:11:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:673965,675133}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.35,0:11:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:688354,689647}Ah, Ms. Kitajima.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.64,0:11:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:689647,692483}You're up now.\NHurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:692483,693902}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.86,0:11:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:697864,699407}Sorry for being late.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.40,0:11:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:699407,702869}Your Helen is different from hers,\Nso everyone is looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.70,0:11:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:703703,705622}Ah, t-thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.62,0:11:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:705622,706206}Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.20,0:11:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:706206,707332}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.29,0:11:56.71,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:713296,716716}Backstage
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.50,0:11:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:713504,716716}Excuse me, can I have\Nsome hot tea and rice cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.92,0:12:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:718927,721846}You too, Ayumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.84,0:12:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:721846,725183}I'll have nothing\Nto do with her acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.18,0:12:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:725183,727894}I can't understand you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:28.16,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:742283,748164}Maya's acting was contrary\Nto Ayumi's perfect acting, something atypical.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.16,0:12:33.16,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:748164,753169}Others couldn't take their eyes off\Nher acting, packed full of emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.58,0:12:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:753586,757298}Oh, did it hurt?\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.29,0:12:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757298,758800}No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.84,0:12:42.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:760843,762345}She's a hard one to act with.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.34,0:12:48.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:762345,768309}I wonder why, but even I'm drawn\Ninto her acting, her pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.10,0:12:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769102,770310}Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.02,0:12:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771020,772230}Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.23,0:12:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:772230,774607}We'll start the miracle scene\Nnext week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.60,0:12:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:774607,775608}Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.60,0:12:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:775608,778694}Thank you.\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.27,0:13:01.15,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:779279,781155}The miracle scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.15,0:13:08.45,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:781155,788454}It's a scene where Helen touches the running\Nwell water and remembers the word "water",
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.45,0:13:12.20,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:788454,792208}which she heard\Nwhen she was six months old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.20,0:13:17.88,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:792208,797880}It's the climax of the play where\Nshe finally learns that things have names.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.63,0:13:24.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:799632,804512}After showering in well water,\NHelen remembers it and learns that it's "water".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.43,0:13:30.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:807432,810810}The miracle Annie Sullivan\Nbrought to Helen…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.81,0:13:33.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:810810,813938}How can I express it? How?
Comment: 0,0:13:41.90,0:13:41.90,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:821904,821904}Eyecatch
Comment: 0,0:13:45.78,0:13:45.78,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:825783,825783}#Eyecatch
Comment: 0,0:13:48.74,0:13:48.74,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:828745,828745}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.50,0:13:57.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:834500,837420}Water…\NWater…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.17,0:14:02.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841174,842342}Water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.76,0:14:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:844761,846721}What are you doing, Maya!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.38,0:14:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:847387,849140}Really, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.55,0:14:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:849557,852518}You'll flood the apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.68,0:14:14.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:853686,854853}Water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.02,0:14:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:858024,860943}Ayumi.\NIt's your grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.61,0:14:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:862612,864947}I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.41,0:14:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:870411,872205}What's this sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.75,0:14:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:875750,876959}Young lady…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.75,0:14:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:877752,880128}Water, water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.17,0:14:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:883174,886469}It's okay, grandma.\NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.93,0:14:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:894935,896354}Water…!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.73,0:15:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:898731,902318}The opening day\Nis finally coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.31,0:15:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:902318,903945}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.94,0:15:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:903945,910576}I've heard that quite a few judges\Nfrom the Academy will be there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.57,0:15:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:910576,914247}Good. It would be great\Nto win some awards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.24,0:15:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:914247,918084}It would give an even greater reputation\Nto the name of Metropolitan Entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.08,0:15:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:918084,919544}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.54,0:15:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919544,927343}The success of the play depends on how the\Ntwo Helens will play the climactic miracle scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.97,0:15:32.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:930972,932849}Wa… ter…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.64,0:15:38.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:937645,938396}I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.43,0:15:42.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:939439,942608}The emotion Helen feels\Nat that miracle moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.48,0:15:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:945486,949574}The word "water", which she suddenly remembers\Nwhen she touched the water from the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.15,0:15:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:951159,953828}How can I express it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.70,0:15:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:954704,956747}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.95,0:16:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:959959,961627}The cord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:967717,969510}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.51,0:16:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:969510,971220}Young lady?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.85,0:16:19.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:976851,979687}This is it.\NThis is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.68,0:16:22.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:979687,982982}Helen's miracle moment:\Nshe's electrified by the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.11,0:16:32.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:988112,992366}I can do it.\NMy Helen, the miracle moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.20,0:16:36.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:995203,996704}Water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.70,0:16:38.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:996704,998039}Water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.03,0:16:40.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:998039,1000373}Water…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.16,0:16:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1003169,1004670}Ryu, come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.83,0:16:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1005838,1007840}Okay, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.05,0:17:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1017058,1020019}I'm… I'm sorry, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.01,0:17:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1020019,1021187}Ryu, apologize to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.89,0:17:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1021896,1024649}I'm sorry, Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.56,0:17:10.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1025566,1030196}Water! Helen was just like\Na water balloon before it exploded.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.19,0:17:18.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1030196,1038538}Filled so much with the word "water" that\Nshe was ready to explode with just a little trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.28,0:17:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1039288,1041249}Uhh…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.24,0:17:23.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1041249,1043751}I can do it.\NMy Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:29.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1043751,1049715}{\t(4464,5964,2,\1c&H101010&\3c&H101010&\4c&H101010&)}The moment that the water balloon hit me,\Nthat was the miracle moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.55,0:17:33.97,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1050550,1053970}The new building\Nof Metropolitan Entertainment
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:36.43,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1053970,1056430}and "The Miracle Worker"\Nhave both opened for their first day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.76,0:17:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1057765,1062144}Wow, famous critics,\Ndirectors and actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.14,0:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1062144,1063604}What a crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.60,0:17:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1063604,1066607}Judges from the Academy\Nare here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.14,0:17:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1067149,1068484}Hey, where's Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.48,0:17:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1068484,1070361}I wonder where she is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.36,0:17:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1070361,1072572}The staff is supposed\Nto be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.53,0:18:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1077534,1080621}Please, take your seat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.62,0:18:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1080621,1082665}No, I'm just fine here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.66,0:18:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1082665,1084041}B-But…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.04,0:18:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1084041,1086002}I have a ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.00,0:18:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1086002,1089380}I can directly see the stage\Nstraight from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.38,0:18:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1089380,1090965}I will stand here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.00,0:18:21.26,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1093009,1101267}Himekawa Utako's Annie Sullivan, Ayumi's Helen:\Nthe first day of the play was proceeding perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.56,0:18:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1107565,1110192}May I serve you some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.03,0:18:35.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1114030,1115698}Hayami Masumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.99,0:18:37.65,Retrospective,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1115990,1117658}…greeting and politeness\Nare much more important.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.15,0:18:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1118159,1120036}H-Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.03,0:18:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1120036,1123122}You seem to be doing fine,\Nas always.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.54,0:18:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126542,1128794}W-What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.79,0:18:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1128794,1130504}I'm greeting you politely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.50,0:18:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1130504,1132840}Oh, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:18:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1132840,1135217}Thank you for your\Npolite greeting, Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.21,0:18:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1135217,1138012}By the way,\Nmay I sit next to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.01,0:18:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138012,1139764}Y-Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.93,0:19:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1141932,1144143}That taiyaki looks delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.14,0:19:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1144143,1146687}May I have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.68,0:19:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1146687,1147688}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.68,0:19:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1147688,1148898}Oh, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.89,0:19:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148898,1151859}I'll be thirsty,\Nso let me get us a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.07,0:19:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1161077,1163537}Why don't you see her play?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.53,0:19:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1163537,1165956}I don't want to see her play.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.95,0:19:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1165956,1171087}I have yet to see her Helen\Neven at practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.62,0:19:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1171629,1174757}I don't want to be stuck\Nwith Ayumi's Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.75,0:19:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1174757,1177009}I have my own Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.00,0:19:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1177009,1181055}I see. But you can't leave the lobby\Nbecause you can't stop thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.26,0:19:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1182264,1185976}I wanted to ask you,\Nwhy are you so into acting?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.52,0:19:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1187520,1193567}Don't you want to live your life freely,\Nrather than acting out someone else's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.56,0:19:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1193567,1198406}Don't you want to live a happy life\Nas an ordinary girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.45,0:20:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1201450,1202493}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.49,0:20:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1202493,1207206}I don't know…\Nwhat's happiness and what's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.87,0:20:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1208874,1215756}All I know is that when I act, I feel something hot\Nin my chest, and feel courage growing in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.34,0:20:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1217341,1224724}"I can do this", a feeling like that comes\Nto me, and I feel happy being alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.68,0:20:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1225683,1230688}My dream is to become an actress\Nwho can play "The Crimson Goddess".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.06,0:20:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1231063,1236652}I feel like that nearly impossible dream\Ncan come true someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.48,0:20:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1238487,1240239}I envy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.23,0:20:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1240239,1241198}Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.19,0:20:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1241198,1243826}Mr. Masumi.\NHere you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.82,0:20:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1243826,1245202}There's an urgent call for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.20,0:20:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1245202,1246412}Oh, I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.99,0:20:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1247996,1250875}Thank you for the taiyaki.\NI used to eat it all the time as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.42,0:21:02.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1260426,1262052}Did I hear him wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:04.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1262052,1264764}I thought he said\Nhe envies me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.76,0:21:10.47,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1265765,1270478}Ayumi played\Nthe perfect Helen that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.47,0:21:14.81,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1270478,1274815}Her Helen was in sync with\NMs. Sullivan, played by her mother, Utako,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.81,0:21:19.23,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1274815,1279236}giving the audience\Noverwhelming emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.07,0:21:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1280070,1282740}Helen folded\Nher napkins on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.19,0:21:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1283199,1285659}Helen folded\Nher own napkins!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.49,0:21:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1288496,1291624}Helen folded the napkins!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.46,0:21:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1294460,1297004}Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.73,0:21:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1314730,1316524}It's still the middle\Nof the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.52,0:22:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1316524,1320319}The judges from the Academy\Nare clapping, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.65,0:22:07.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1324657,1327576}I want to win an Academy Award\Nno matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.57,0:22:15.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1327576,1335000}With Himekawa Utako and Ayumi…\NKitajima Maya is no comparison to Ayumi's acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.66,0:22:22.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1335668,1342550}I will show Tsukikage who is really\Nappropriate for "The Crimson Goddess".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.18,0:22:35.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1354186,1355020}Ayumi…
